&lt;div class="csaf-accordion-content"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An OS Command injection vulnerability exists in XWEB Pro version 1.12.1 and prior, enabling an authenticated attacker to achieve remote code execution on the system by configuring a maliciously crafted LCD state which is later processed during system setup, enabling remote code execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-25037"&gt;View CVE Details&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Affected Products&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;Copeland XWEB and XWEB Pro&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;div class="ics-vendor-version-status"&gt;
